%FUNCTION  :+This Edit macro invoke the print of the data you are editin
             current edit file).
%SYNTAX :+   PEDIT or PEDIT HELP or H
%USE :+      Type%PEDIT+on the COMMAND line, eventually mark a range of
             with the "C" range command on the line numbers, and press E
             Immediately, you will be prompted to supply the print optio
            %Carriage CC+= NO/YES to say if first character is data or C
            %SYSOUT Class+= the class in which output is to be queued fo
                            print. Default is A.
            %Copies+= the number of copies to be printed. Default is 1.
            %Output status+= HOLD/NOHOLD to place or not the output on a
                            Queue upon deallocation. Default is NOHOLD.
            %RMT destination+= Remote Station to which the output (sysou
                            to be routed (i.e. R41). Default is LOCAL.
             Then all or only the range of lines you have selected from
             current editing file are printed.
)PROC
  &ZCONT = PAJTPED
)END
